<%= section "Organizing course material into topics" do %>

<p>As described above, OST enables you to sort your course materials into <em>topics</em>. How you organize your topics is up to you. 
  
    <li>Learning conditions, if any, set for your class</li>  
  <li>Structure of assignments: how many assignments? how many topic(s) will each assignment cover?
</p>

Why learning conditions matter 

A learning condition is a set of rules that you tell OST to apply when building assignments. An example of a learning condition is: each assignment pulls 50% of its questions from the current topic and 50% of its questions from the previous topic. 

